{
  "stem": "2533.1",
  "chunk_idx": 12,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 8.9,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 95,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "They probably, you know, maybe Saturday they used to get together somewhere for-- for Friday night.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 95,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And it wasn't much of a celebration then or-- for holidays, but the Rosh Hashanah, Erev Rosh Hashanah, my eldest brother passed away, and it was so tragic because all day he was cleaning the bricks from the synagogue.",
      "word_count": 39
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 95,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "It was a very hot day.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 95,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "It was September-- the 11th of September.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 95,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And when he came home, he didn't feel well.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 95,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And it was-- the next day was Rosh Hashanah, and he went to bed early.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 95,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And then he got the middle about 2 o'clock in the morning a heart attack.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 95,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "And we were not allowed to go out.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 95,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "We had to wait for the sentry to come along with the German soldier as police or whatever they were, and then we could go and call a doctor.",
      "word_count": 29
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 95,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "But by the time we come along, there were not any way to get a-- to get out to-- to go even to call somebody over to go and fetch the doctor.",
      "word_count": 32
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 95,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "By the time the doctor came, he couldn't help him anymore.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 96,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Oh, no hospital, no.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 96,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Even if there would have been a hospital, if the doctor would've come early enough, he could have helped him because we had, from Austria, doctors, you know, all the people who were evacuated from-- from Germany or the, you know, during the war.",
      "word_count": 44
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 96,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And the Austrian doctor was still in the-- he was in the ghetto too.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 96,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "He said, if he would have been able to come earlier, but we didn't know about him.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 96,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "He said, he had very high blood pressure, and that's what-- it killed him.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 96,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "He was very tall.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 96,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And that maybe was, you know-- he was standing, going for work, everybody could see him.",
      "word_count": 16
    }
  ],
